{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"NNC"}],"externalID":"s:3NNC12ModelBuilderC","title":"ModelBuilder","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ModelBuilder","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ModelBuilder","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Class","symbolKind":"class"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/nnc\/modelbuilder"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ModelBuilder","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"T","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A model builder on the other hand doesn’t have that restriction. When input changes,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it simply calls the given builder closure to construct a new model. In such way,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you can continue to use reshape etc to assume fixed inputs and outputs, it will just","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"work for dynamic inputs. The newly built model will carry over stateful components","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(parameters) from the old models, thus, it doesn’t reset your training. This also means","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you need to make sure parameter shape won’t change when input changes, otherwise we","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will fatal.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/Mod